---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for List Hygiene in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for list hygiene by suppression, consent, engagement segments, deliverability, pricing context, sources, and practical tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Large stores needing granular engagement and suppression','Detailed profiles, events, and conditional segments','Data governance and reputation work remain substantial','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail teams managing campaign engagement and SMS opt-outs','Accessible audience and automation controls','Volume spikes require disciplined cleanup','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean teams maintaining a focused email list','Simple sequences and low operational overhead','Less advanced hygiene reporting should be checked','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Marketing and transactional lists with clear separation','Broad messaging and contact options','Streams and suppression require QA','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores sending modest newsletters','Native customer and campaign setup','Limited advanced engagement governance','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">List hygiene is a recurring operating practice: record consent, suppress opt-outs, remove invalid addresses, review engagement, and understand why a segment is being mailed. A clean list is not simply a smaller list.</p><p>We prioritize suppression, source quality, engagement review, authentication, and clear separation between marketing and transactional streams. Confirm current vendor guidance and pricing from official sources before changing sending volume.</p><h2>Shortlist for list hygiene</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First hygiene project</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Engagement and suppression map':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Campaign-quality review':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Source and sequence audit':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Marketing/transactional split':'Consent and bounce review'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for list hygiene</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} can help when the store documents source, consent, suppression, engagement, and ownership. The platform cannot guarantee inbox placement; sender reputation and responsible collection remain merchant responsibilities.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with a monthly hygiene review covering bounces, complaints, unsubscribes, inactive cohorts, authentication, and flow exclusions. Measure delivery and customer experience, not just open rates or list size.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a deliverability-aware operating test; can use Shopify signals.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; audience, seats, sends, and infrastructure affect cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans, contacts, sends, seats, support, authentication, and SMS pricing.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Hygiene priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Granular engagement suppression</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible profile and segment controls.</td></tr><tr><td>Focused low-volume list</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Simple operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Marketing/transactional separation</td><td>Brevo</td><td>Broad messaging orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Continue with the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/deliverability">deliverability guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
